    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1217"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1217">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/284.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Relative demands local Constitutional authorities based on instructions of
                    Minister Hacienda F. Villareal that bar-taxes be paid in Mexican gold or United
                    States gold at two for one which is practically demand for payment in United
                    States gold as there is no Mexican gold available. One or two oil companies rely
                    upon decree number twenty-one dated at Nogales, February 28, 1914, and signed by
                    Venustiano Carranza, making it obligatory upon officials as well as the public
                    to accept Constitutionalist bills. Have tendered such bills in payment of
                    bar-taxes. Local officials have taken matter up with General Carranza.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
